g.text: - A container for storing data values
- Variables allow us to name data and use it throughout the program
- Type: specifies the kind of data that variable will store (int)
- Identifier: The name of the variable (score)
- Initial Value: The value assigned to the variable at the time of
- Integer types (int) store only whole numbers (100)
- variables must be initialized before reading their values
- Variables can be updated after initialisation
- You can assign the value of one variable to anoter
- Multiple variables of the same type can be declared in one line,
- However, it is better to declare variables separately for better
